track_notes: The first 5km is on the forest road. At the top of the pass there is a gate and stile. By reputation this is hard walking in mud and tussocks. I was lucky and went in a dry spell. There was cattle grazing the hillside. The cattle had left assorted tracks which made the walking easier in the dry weather. Walk time about 2hr but allow 3h for stops and route finding.
This is the full track for the day. With the right weather it is a possible trip. Dry conditions are the key issue. The drive time is about 1h30m, it could be shortened if the forest drive is open.
track_title: Both Craiglee -150 -152 summits in a day
